anks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Late Latin name <i>Constantinus</i>, a derivative of <i>Constans</i>;  see  Constant .  In early modern English the names <i>Constant</i> and <i>Constantine</i> were not always clearly distinguished. The Roman emperor  Constantine the Great  (  ?288–337 ) is specially honoured in the Christian Church as the first Christian emperor. The name was also borne by three kings of medieval Scotland, where it represents an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name   Conn  , and is a traditional name in the Phipps (Marquesses of Normanby) family."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Constantine de Clifton was born in 1338, in Buckenham, Norfolk, England, his father, Sir Adam de Clifton Baron Clifton de Buckenham, was 32 and his mother, Eleanor de Mortimer, was 24. He married Catherine de la Pole in 1351, in Buckenham, Norfolk, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died before 20 January 1363, in his hometown."},"et":{"1338–before 20 January 1363":"1338–enne 20. jaanuari 1363","1323–Female":"1323–Surnud","1330–1411":"1330–1411","1333–1403":"1333–1403","1338–1363":"1338–1363","1350–1411":"1350–1411","1332–1363":"1332–1363","1353–1388":"1353–1388","1362–Male":"1362–Surnud","1306–1367":"1306–1367","1314–1360":"1314–1360","before 20 January 1363":"enne 20. jaanuari 1363","1363":"1363","1330":"1330","1351":"1351","1362":"1362","1350":"1350","1360":"1360","1338":"1338","1316":"1316","1403":"1403","1314":"1314","1367":"1367","1411":"1411","1323":"1323","1388":"1388","1333":"1333","1332":"1332","1353":"1353","1306":"1306","Buckenham, Norfolk, England":"Buckenham, Norfolk, England","Paston, Norfolk, England":"Paston, Norfolk, England","United Kingdom":"United Kingdom","Buckenham Castle, Norfolk, England":"Buckenham, Norfolk, England","Castle Buckenham, Norfolk, England":"Buckenham, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"1338–before 20 January 1363":"1338–ennen vuotta 20. tammikuuta 1363","1323–Female":"1323–Kuollut","1330–141